<div class="page-section">
<h2>Career Compass for secondary schools</h2>
<p>Career Compass is designed to complement your existing careers program — not replace it. It gives students a structured, psychologically grounded starting point for career conversations that your counsellors can build on.</p>
<p>Unlike traditional aptitude-based tools, Career Compass asks who a student is, not what they can do on a timed test. This makes it particularly effective for students who don't perform well under pressure — including neurodiverse students, school refusers, and those with anxiety.</p>
</div>
<div class="page-section">
<h2>How schools use Career Compass</h2>
<div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-icon">&#x1F4CB;</div><div class="info-card-title">Year 9 &amp; 10 subject selection</div><div class="info-card-desc">Help students choose senior subjects with a clearer sense of direction. Career Compass surfaces values and interests that inform subject choice conversations.</div></div>
<div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-icon">&#x1F393;</div><div class="info-card-title">Year 11 &amp; 12 career planning</div><div class="info-card-desc">Give senior students a personalised career map they can bring into counsellor appointments. Career Compass includes ATAR and non-ATAR pathways, apprenticeships and TAFE routes.</div></div>
<div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-icon">&#x1F9E0;</div><div class="info-card-title">VCE VM and applied learning</div><div class="info-card-desc">Career Compass is particularly well-suited to VCE VM cohorts. The assessment is conversational, not test-based, and the results include practical, work-ready pathways alongside further study options.</div></div>
<div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-icon">&#x1F91D;</div><div class="info-card-title">Student wellbeing integration</div><div class="info-card-desc">The Sensitive Explorer Protocol identifies students who need calm, structured environments — without requiring disclosure. Results for these students are filtered to avoid overwhelming or competitive settings.</div></div>
</div>
<div class="page-section">
<h2>Methodology</h2>
<p>Career Compass is grounded in established career development theory, including Holland's RIASEC model, Super's life-span theory and Savickas's career construction approach. The assessment uses ipsative measurement (forced-choice pairs) to reduce social desirability bias — students answer what feels true, not what sounds impressive.</p>
<p>The tool differentiates itself from platforms like Morrisby through its AI personalisation layer — every result is written specifically for the student, referencing what they actually told us — and through its explicit design for neurodiverse and disengaged young people.</p>
</div>
<div class="page-section">
<h2>Pilot program</h2>
<p>We are currently offering pilot access to a small number of Australian secondary schools. Pilot schools receive free access for their student cohort, a debrief with our team, and the opportunity to shape the product roadmap.</p>
<div class="highlight-box"><p>&#x1F4E7; To discuss a pilot, contact us at <a href="mailto:schools@careercompass.com.au">schools@careercompass.com.au</a> or <a href="/contact">complete our contact form</a>. We typically respond within 2 business days.</p></div>
